  "properties": {
    "title": "Introducing contributors-img: Keep contributors in README.md",
    "date": "2019-03-29T00:00:00.000Z",
    "tags": ["GitHub", "OSS"]
  },
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Hey folks! I introduce a web app I’ve created, ",
          "annotations": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "contributors-img",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ". It generate an image to display contributors of your GitHub repository.",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "external": true,
      "url": "https://thepracticaldev.s3.amazonaws.com/i/2by6h6z64d79gka4ncsd.png",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "link_preview",
      "url": "https://contrib.rocks/"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Why image?",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Because images are only way to embed dynamic content in README.md on GitHub.",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Once you paste the generated image’s URL in README.md, it will keep contributors list in sync without any effort.",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "It’s FREE to use for open source! And if you love it, please donate me via ",
          "annotations": {}
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Patreon",
          "href": "https://www.patreon.com/lacolaco",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Technically, contributors-img is built on top of Google Cloud Functions / Puppeteer / Angular / GitHub APIs.",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Caveats",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulleted_list",
      "items": [
        {
          "type": "bulleted_list_item",
          "text": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A repo having too many contributors takes a long time to generate an image.",
              "annotations": {}
            }
          ],
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "type": "bulleted_list_item",
          "text": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "For each repository, images are generated once in a day and it will be cached for later requests.",
              "annotations": {}
            }
          ],
          "children": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Thanks!",
          "annotations": {}
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
